---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import AnimatedCard from "../../components/AnimatedCard.jsx";
---

<MainLayout title="The Challenge | Riding4GBS">
  <AnimatedCard client:load>
    <div
      class="m-4 md:m-12 p-6 md:p-10 bg-white rounded-xl max-w-4xl w-full mx-auto text-gray-800 font-sans bg-opacity-70"
    >
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          Conquering the Pyrenees: The Route ðŸšµ
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          This is not just a bike ride; it's a complete coast-to-coast traverse
          of one of the world's most formidable mountain ranges.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 md:gap-8 text-center my-10 border-y py-6"
      >
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600">21</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Total Days</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600">1,685</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Kilometres</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600">34,900</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Metres of Climbing</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600">4+x</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The Height of Everest</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          The Style: A Self-Supported Journey
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-left">
          This challenge is a journey back to basics, undertaken in a
          self-supported bikepacking style. I'll be carrying all my own
          equipment, relying on the kindness of the community I meet along the
          way. While the logistical test is a personal one, the road itself is
          open to all. I would be honoured and motivated to have local riders
          join me for a few kilometres or to share the effort on a classic
          mountain pass. This journey is about community, and I welcome anyone
          who wants to be a part of it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-12">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
            Leg 1: The Epic Crossing
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The journey begins by heading east from the Basque Country,
            following the path of the Tour de France legends. This first leg of
            the journey crosses into France to conquer icons like the Col du
            Tourmalet before tackling "The Pinnacle"â€”the Port d'Envalira in
            Andorra. It is a pure test of climbing strength on the road to the
            Mediterranean.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
            Leg 2: The Journey Home
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Upon reaching the coast, the goal is to turn back west and begin the
            long journey home. This is a test of endurance and resilience. The
            return route will focus on the Spanish side, tackling the long,
            remote, and beautiful roads of the Pre-Pyrenees in Catalunya,
            AragÃ³n, and finally, Navarra. The climbs are less steep but just as
            relentless, demanding a different kind of strength for the long road
            back.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </AnimatedCard>
</MainLayout>
